Add a public function called GetNothing to Calculator.calr that always returns None. It takes no parameters and returns Option<i32>.

Use this exact Calor Option None return syntax:
§F{f003:GetNothing:pub}
  §O{Option<i32>}
  §R §NN
§/F{f003}

The Option type syntax:
- §R §NN - returns None
- §NN represents the absence of a value
- Safer alternative to null in C#
